    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix thread-unsafe access in M2AP eNB management procedures\n\n### Summary\nThe M2AP module contains several functions that access global/shared data structures without proper synchronization, leading to potential race conditions and data corruption when multiple threads access these functions concurrently. This issue manifests as intermittent segmentation faults and inconsistent eNB state reporting during M2 setup procedures.\n\nThe problem occurs in functions that iterate through the global `m2ap_eNB_internal_data` structure using STAILQ and RB tree macros. Without mutex protection, concurrent access can result in:\n- Segmentation faults when one thread modifies the data structure while another is traversing it\n- Inconsistent results from lookup functions\n- Corruption of the internal eNB instance lists\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/M2AP/m2ap_eNB_management_procedures.c`: \n  * Added pthread mutex to protect global `m2ap_eNB_internal_data` structure\n  * Added proper locking/unlocking around all functions accessing shared data:\n    - `m2ap_is_eNB_pci_in_list`\n    - `m2ap_is_eNB_id_in_list` \n    - `m2ap_is_eNB_assoc_id_in_list`\n    - `m2ap_get_eNB`\n    - `m2ap_eNB_get_instance`\n    - `m2ap_dump_eNB_list`\n  * Used goto-based cleanup pattern to ensure mutex is always unlocked exactly once\n  * Added error handling for mutex operations using existing M2AP logging macros\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce this issue:\n1. Configure multiple eNBs to establish M2 connections simultaneously\n2. Monitor logs for intermittent segmentation faults during M2 setup procedures\n3. Observe inconsistent eNB state reporting when querying eNB information concurrently from multiple threads\n4. Run with thread sanitizer to detect data races in the M2AP management functions\n\nThe issue is most likely to occur under high load conditions with multiple concurrent M2 setup requests or when external management interfaces query eNB state information simultaneously with ongoing M2 procedures.\n"
}